<p>This is what Android’s default stock lockscreen widget should’ve been. Love it.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/bulknews/~4/7jaZGMFXVC0\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (link nil "http://feeds.bulknews.net/~r/bulknews/~3/7jaZGMFXVC0/43215699687") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://weblog.bulknews.net/post/43215699687") (pubDate nil "Sat, 16 Feb 2013 01:23:53 -0800") (feedburner:origLink nil "http://weblog.bulknews.net/post/43215699687")) (item nil (title nil "Nexus 4 wireless charger (aka orb)") (description nil "<p>I was afraid this dock charger won&#8217;t be out forever, but finally here it comes.</p>

<p><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/bulknews/8478150162/\" title=\"P1130518_DxO by miyagawa, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8106/8478150162_bf85a9a82b_b.jpg\" width=\"512\" alt=\"P1130518_DxO\"/></a></p>

<p><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/bulknews/8478155586/\" title=\"P1130528_DxO by miyagawa, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8088/8478155586_a64b58ea3d_b.jpg\" width=\"512\" alt=\"P1130528_DxO\"/></a></p>

<p>It&#8217;s really handy that i can just leave the phone on the dock without plugging in the silly micro USB plug (there&#8217;s of course upside down). Amazing stuff.</p>

<p>The charger is apparently compatible to Qi, so it can probably charge other Nokia phones, as well as Panasonic&#8217;s USB batteries.</p>

<p><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/bulknews/8478158142/\" title=\"P1130529_DxO by miyagawa, on Flickr\"><img src=\"http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8087/8478158142_d57613345a_b.jpg\" width=\"512\" alt=\"P1130529_DxO\"/></a></p>

<p>The slight issue that  I now have is that this is an <em>extra</em> cable on my desk, in addition to lightning, 30-pin <em>and</em> micro-USB to charge other gadgets, not replacing them.</p>

<p>First world problems, really.</p>

<p><strong>UPDATE</strong>: Now i have two (serious) issues with this charger.</p>

<p>1) The phone&#8217;s vibration makes a big noise when it&#8217;s put on top of this charger, because the dock strengthens the vibration. It&#8217;ll be a serious issue for some push notifications during the night.</p>

<p>2) The charge often suddenly stops, and when I put the phone back it won&#8217;t charge again, until when I unplug and plug the micro USB cable in the back. I thought this is an issue of crappy micro USB cables, but i tried with 4 different micro USB cables and it happened with every one of them, which leads me to believe that this is either the charger or the nexus 4 phone hardware itself that is the issue.</p>

<p>Another round of returning and getting a replacement? Not fun.</p>

<p><strong>UPDATE 2</strong>: I did more experiments with more cables and more power bricks, and found that the power brick that came with the charger was <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F8jLGrkZyFc&amp;feature=youtu.be\">the faulty one</a>. I&#8217;m now using the power brick that came with nexus 4 and it works much more reliably.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/bulknews/~4/8f-u0FOYHPA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (link nil "http://feeds.bulknews.net/~r/bulknews/~3/8f-u0FOYHPA/43203547470") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://weblog.bulknews.net/post/43203547470") (pubDate nil "Fri, 15 Feb 2013 20:44:00 -0800") (feedburner:origLink nil "http://weblog.bulknews.net/post/43203547470")) (item nil (title nil "A bug report from aaronsw") (description nil "<a href=\"https://github.com/miyagawa/cpanminus/issues/158\">A bug report from aaronsw</a>: <p>When I heard the news of Aaron Swartz, it felt like I’ve done some conversation with him online <em>quite recently</em>, despite that i haven’t met him in person. However I didn’t bother searching my inbox - today I did, and this shows up. 8 months ago.</p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/bulknews/~4/PHeb96YQ8qI\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (link nil "http://feeds.bulknews.net/~r/bulknews/~3/PHeb96YQ8qI/43133901858") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://weblog.bulknews.net/post/43133901858") (pubDate nil "Thu, 14 Feb 2013 22:25:00 -0800") (feedburner:origLink nil "http://weblog.bulknews.net/post/43133901858")) (item nil (title nil "Podcast 登録のしかた") (description nil "<p>RSS を使った購読がわかりにくいというご意見をいくつかもらったので、簡単にご紹介。</p>

